                            </div>
                            <p>
                                While you can spend hours immersing yourself in Grammar stuff and textbooks, it sadly won’t take you too far when faced with having an actual conversation.  There’s nothing like speaking a language in the moment with another person, having to decipher tone and words and body language all at once.  But the best way to learn to speak German as opposed to writing it is to do just that— speak it! If you cann’t get in touch with native speakers or might have fear of being embarrassed of making mistakes in front of others, then you can try 
